│ MemorySSA rightly returns nullptr for non-memory-touching instructions, but   │
│ the MemorySSAUpdater currently assumes creation must succeed and triggers the │
│ assert.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n- The log shows LICM decides to sink the  │
│ instruction and prints: \"LICM sinking instruction:   %i3 = call i32          │
│ @bar()\".\n- The crash happens when cloneInstructionInExitBlock calls         │
│ MSSAU.createMemoryAccessInBB for the cloned call.\n- The assertion message:   │
│ \"Tried to create a memory access for a non-memory touching instruction\"     │
│ confirms MemorySSA detected the call as memory(none).\n\n3. Root Cause        │
│ Analysis:\n- MemorySSA::createDefinedAccess has a parameter                   │
│ CreationMustSucceed defaulting to true via the header declaration. If the     │
│ instruction neither reads nor writes memory, createNewAccess returns nullptr. │
│ With CreationMustSucceed=true, MemorySSA asserts on nullptr.\n-               │
│ MemorySSAUpdater::createMemoryAccessInBB, createMemoryAccessBefore, and       │
│ createMemoryAccessAfter call MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition) without │
│ specifying CreationMustSucceed=false and immediately try to insert the        │
│ returned access into MemorySSA lists, assuming non-null.\n- LICM's            │
│ cloneInstructionInExitBlock checks whether the original instruction had a     │
│ MemorySSA access and then unconditionally calls createMemoryAccessInBB for    │
│ the clone. For a call with memory(none), the original likely had no access,   │
│ but the code still attempts the creation when                                 │
│ MSSAU.getMemorySSA()->getMemoryAccess(&I) is non-null. In our case, after     │
│ unswitch, the call to @bar is memory(none), so creation must allow nullptr    │
│ and skip insertion.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n- Change MemorySSAUpdater  │
│ methods to allow non-memory-touching instructions by setting                  │
│ CreationMustSucceed=false and guarding insertion on a null return. This       │
│ central fix ensures all users (LICM, GVN, LoopIdiomRecognize, LoopSink,       │
│ SimpleLoopUnswitch, etc.) won't hit the assertion when handling memory(none)  │
│ instructions.\n\nEdit 1:                                                      │
│ llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp:1404-1410\nReplace unconditional       │
│ creation and insertion with a version that allows nullptr and skips           │
