│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs due to an assertion in MemorySSA::createDefinedAccess that   │
│ is designed to catch attempts to create a MemorySSA access for an instruction │
│ that does not touch memory. In the provided IR, the indirect call becomes a   │
│ direct call to @bar after SimpleLoopUnswitch. The callee @bar has attributes  │
│ nounwind willreturn memory(none), meaning it neither reads nor writes memory. │
│ LICM sinks the call and then attempts to create a MemorySSA access for the    │
│ cloned instruction. MemorySSA rightly returns nullptr for non-memory-touching │
│ instructions, but the MemorySSAUpdater currently assumes creation must        │
│ succeed and triggers the assert.                                              │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ - The log shows LICM decides to sink the instruction and prints: "LICM        │
│ sinking instruction:   %i3 = call i32 @bar()".                                │
│ - The crash happens when cloneInstructionInExitBlock calls                    │
│ MSSAU.createMemoryAccessInBB for the cloned call.                             │
│ - The assertion message: "Tried to create a memory access for a non-memory    │
│ touching instruction" confirms MemorySSA detected the call as memory(none).   │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ - MemorySSA::createDefinedAccess has a parameter CreationMustSucceed          │
│ defaulting to true via the header declaration. If the instruction neither     │
│ reads nor writes memory, createNewAccess returns nullptr. With                │
│ CreationMustSucceed=true, MemorySSA asserts on nullptr.                       │
│ - MemorySSAUpdater::createMemoryAccessInBB, createMemoryAccessBefore, and     │
│ createMemoryAccessAfter call MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition) without │
│ specifying CreationMustSucceed=false and immediately try to insert the        │
│ returned access into MemorySSA lists, assuming non-null.                      │
│ - LICM's cloneInstructionInExitBlock checks whether the original instruction  │
│ had a MemorySSA access and then unconditionally calls createMemoryAccessInBB  │
│ for the clone. For a call with memory(none), the original likely had no       │
│ access, but the code still attempts the creation when                         │
│ MSSAU.getMemorySSA()->getMemoryAccess(&I) is non-null. In our case, after     │
│ unswitch, the call to @bar is memory(none), so creation must allow nullptr    │
│ and skip insertion.                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - Change MemorySSAUpdater methods to allow non-memory-touching instructions   │
│ by setting CreationMustSucceed=false and guarding insertion on a null return. │
│ This central fix ensures all users (LICM, GVN, LoopIdiomRecognize, LoopSink,  │
│ SimpleLoopUnswitch, etc.) won't hit the assertion when handling memory(none)  │
│ instructions.                                                                 │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit 1: llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp:1404-1410                      │
│ Replace unconditional creation and insertion with a version that allows       │
│ nullptr and skips insertion.                                                  │
│                                                                               │
│ Before:                                                                       │
│   MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess = MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition);       │
│   MSSA->insertIntoListsForBlock(NewAccess, BB, Point);                        │
│   return NewAccess;                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ After:                                                                        │
│   MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess =                                                 │
│       MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition, /*Template=*/nullptr,          │
│                                 /*CreationMustSucceed=*/false);               │
│   if (NewAccess)                                                              │
│     MSSA->insertIntoListsForBlock(NewAccess, BB, Point);                      │
│   return NewAccess;                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit 2: llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp:1416-1420                      │
│ Apply the same logic to createMemoryAccessBefore.                             │
│                                                                               │
│ Before:                                                                       │
│   MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess = MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition);       │
│   MSSA->insertIntoListsBefore(NewAccess, InsertPt->getBlock(),                │
│                               InsertPt->getIterator());                       │
│   return NewAccess;                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ After:                                                                        │
│   MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess =                                                 │
│       MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition, /*Template=*/nullptr,          │
│                                 /*CreationMustSucceed=*/false);               │
│   if (NewAccess)                                                              │
│     MSSA->insertIntoListsBefore(NewAccess, InsertPt->getBlock(),              │
│                                 InsertPt->getIterator());                     │
│   return NewAccess;                                                           │
│                                                                               │
│ Edit 3: llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp:1426-1430                      │
