  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs due to an
assertion in MemorySSA::createDefinedAccess that is designed to catch attempts to
create a MemorySSA access for an instruction that does not touch memory. In the
provided IR, the indirect call becomes a direct call to @bar after
SimpleLoopUnswitch. The callee @bar has attributes nounwind willreturn
memory(none), meaning it neither reads nor writes memory. LICM sinks the call and
then attempts to create a MemorySSA access for the cloned instruction. MemorySSA
rightly returns nullptr for non-memory-touching instructions, but the
MemorySSAUpdater currently assumes creation must succeed and triggers the
assert.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n- The log shows LICM decides to sink the
instruction and prints: \"LICM sinking instruction:   %i3 = call i32 @bar()\".\n-
The crash happens when cloneInstructionInExitBlock calls
MSSAU.createMemoryAccessInBB for the cloned call.\n- The assertion message:
\"Tried to create a memory access for a non-memory touching instruction\"
confirms MemorySSA detected the call as memory(none).\n\n3. Root Cause
Analysis:\n- MemorySSA::createDefinedAccess has a parameter CreationMustSucceed
defaulting to true via the header declaration. If the instruction neither reads
nor writes memory, createNewAccess returns nullptr. With
CreationMustSucceed=true, MemorySSA asserts on nullptr.\n-
MemorySSAUpdater::createMemoryAccessInBB, createMemoryAccessBefore, and
createMemoryAccessAfter call MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition) without
specifying CreationMustSucceed=false and immediately try to insert the returned
access into MemorySSA lists, assuming non-null.\n- LICM's
cloneInstructionInExitBlock checks whether the original instruction had a
MemorySSA access and then unconditionally calls createMemoryAccessInBB for the
clone. For a call with memory(none), the original likely had no access, but the
code still attempts the creation when MSSAU.getMemorySSA()->getMemoryAccess(&I)
is non-null. In our case, after unswitch, the call to @bar is memory(none), so
creation must allow nullptr and skip insertion.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s):\n-
Change MemorySSAUpdater methods to allow non-memory-touching instructions by
setting CreationMustSucceed=false and guarding insertion on a null return. This
central fix ensures all users (LICM, GVN, LoopIdiomRecognize, LoopSink,
SimpleLoopUnswitch, etc.) won't hit the assertion when handling memory(none)
instructions.\n\nEdit 1:
llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp:1404-1410\nReplace unconditional creation
and insertion with a version that allows nullptr and skips
insertion.\n\nBefore:\n  MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess = MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I,
Definition);\n  MSSA->insertIntoListsForBlock(NewAccess, BB, Point);\n  return
NewAccess;\n\nAfter:\n  MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess =\n
MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition, /*Template=*/nullptr,\n
/*CreationMustSucceed=*/false);\n  if (NewAccess)\n
MSSA->insertIntoListsForBlock(NewAccess, BB, Point);\n  return NewAccess;\n\nEdit
2: llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp:1416-1420\nApply the same logic to
createMemoryAccessBefore.\n\nBefore:\n  MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess =
MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition);\n
MSSA->insertIntoListsBefore(NewAccess, InsertPt->getBlock(),\n
InsertPt->getIterator());\n  return NewAccess;\n\nAfter:\n  MemoryUseOrDef
*NewAccess =\n      MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition,
/*Template=*/nullptr,\n
/*CreationMustSucceed=*/false);\n  if (NewAccess)\n
MSSA->insertIntoListsBefore(NewAccess, InsertPt->getBlock(),\n
InsertPt->getIterator());\n  return NewAccess;\n\nEdit 3:
llvm/lib/Analysis/MemorySSAUpdater.cpp:1426-1430\nApply the same logic to
createMemoryAccessAfter.\n\nBefore:\n  MemoryUseOrDef *NewAccess =
MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition);\n
MSSA->insertIntoListsBefore(NewAccess, InsertPt->getBlock(),\n
++InsertPt->getIterator());\n  return NewAccess;\n\nAfter:\n  MemoryUseOrDef
*NewAccess =\n      MSSA->createDefinedAccess(I, Definition,
/*Template=*/nullptr,\n
/*CreationMustSucceed=*/false);\n  if (NewAccess)\n
MSSA->insertIntoListsBefore(NewAccess, InsertPt->getBlock(),\n
++InsertPt->getIterator());\n  return NewAccess;\n\nThese changes make
MemorySSAUpdater resilient to non-memory-touching instructions and prevent the
assertion from firing. Callers already often check for nullptr returns (e.g.,
LICM.cpp:1469-1477), so this integrates smoothly.\n\n5. Conclusion:\nThe crash is
due to attempting to create MemorySSA accesses for calls marked memory(none),
which correctly returns nullptr from MemorySSA but was treated as a hard error by
MemorySSAUpdater. By updating MemorySSAUpdater to pass CreationMustSucceed=false
and guarding insertions with null checks, we avoid the assertion and let LICM and
other passes handle such instructions properly. This fix aligns with MemorySSA
semantics and the existing caller-side null checks, restoring correctness for the
pipeline loop-mssa(simple-loop-unswitch<nontrivial>,licm).",
